Package net.grinder.communication

The Grinder communication subsystem.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
Acceptor.Listener Listener interface.
Address Interface implemented by addresses.
BlockingSender Interface for classes that manage the sending of messages.
Message Marker interface implemented by messages.
MessageDispatchRegistry Register of message handlers, keyed by message type.
QueuedSender Sender that allows messages to be queued.
Receiver Interface for classes that manage the receipt of messages.
ResourcePool A pool of resources.
ResourcePool.Closeable Something that can be closed.
ResourcePool.Listener Listener interface.
ResourcePool.Reservation Public interface to a resource reservation.
ResourcePool.Resource Public interface to a resource.
Sender Interface for classes that manage the sending of messages.
SocketWrapper.ClosedListener Socket event notification interface.
 

Class Summary
AbstractFanOutSender Manages the sending of messages to many Receivers.
AbstractSender Abstract class that manages the sending of messages.
Acceptor Active object that accepts connections on a ServerSocket.
ClientReceiver Manages receipt of messages from a server over a TCP connection.
ClientSender Class that manages the sending of messages to a server.
CloseCommunicationMessage Message used to cleanly indicate that a unicast communication channel should be terminated.
CommunicationDefaults Default communication constants.
ConnectionIdentity Value object that represents the identity of an accepted connection.
ConnectionType Constants that are used to discriminate between different types of connections.
Connector Connection factory.
Connector.ConnectDetails Connection details read from a stream.
FanOutServerSender Manages the sending of messages to many TCP clients.
FanOutStreamSender Manages the sending of messages to many streams.
IgnoreShutdownSender A Sender decorator that ignores shutdown.
MessageDispatchRegistry.AbstractBlockingHandler Most handlers ignore the shutdown event, so provide this as a convenient base for anonymous classes.
MessageDispatchRegistry.AbstractHandler Most handlers ignore the shutdown event, so provide this as a convenient base for anonymous classes.
MessageDispatchSender Passive Senderclass that dispatches incoming messages to the appropriate handler.
MessagePump Active object that copies messages from a Receiver to a Sender.
MessageQueue Thread-safe queue of Messages.
MessageRequiringResponse Pair a Message with a way to send a response.
NoResponseMessage Message indicating that that a blocking send was not handled.
QueuedSenderDecorator QueuedSender implementation.
ResourcePoolImplementation Implementation of ResourcePool.
ServerReceiver Manages the receipt of messages from many clients.
SocketWrapper Wrapper for a Socket that is {ResourcePool.ResourcePool} and understands our connection close protocol.
StreamReceiver Manages receipt of messages from a server over a stream.
StreamSender Class that manages the sending of messages to a server.
TeeSender Passive Sender class that delegates to two other Senders.
 

Exception Summary
Acceptor.ShutdownException Indicates the Acceptor has been shut down.
BlockingSender.NoResponseException Exception indicating that the server chose to send no response back to a BlockingSender.blockingSend(Message).
CommunicationException Exception thrown by communication package.
